// Routing
    It is a mechanism that maps the url request to the controller actions
      - When useer enter the url, MVC routing decides which controller and action will handle the request.
      - Withot routing, MVC Framework wouldnt know which code to execute for the given url.

Key concept: A route defines a pattern for URLs and tells MVC which controller/action to call.

// Why do we need Routing?
Create friendly URLs
	Example: /Products/Details/5 instead of /Products.aspx?id=5
Map URLs to controllers/actions
	The same action can have multiple URLs or patterns.
Support parameterized URLs
	You can pass parameters in the URL itself (like id, category, etc.)
Enable SEO-friendly URLs
	Search engines prefer readable URLs.
